This paper discusses the design and analysis of a new pseudo-random function, which falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). The use of SIMD instructions suggests a focus on efficient implementation, which could also fall under computer architecture (cs.AR) or parallel computing (cs.DC). The discussion of potential applications in file checksums and stream ciphers suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE) or programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the statistical analysis and cryptanalysis could also fall under the category of data structures (cs.DS).
